      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JUMBUK WANG WANG (5) comes off an average run last start when seventh at this track over 425m behind Panther's Way (25.02) in a Grade 5. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. Worth another chance. BURN ALONG (1) has a strong record this trip with 14 wins and eight placings from 38 starts. Below best last time at this track (21.21) in a Grade 5 H, finishing a 17 length eighth. Looks one of the chances. PAW XANTHIE (2) doesn't win out of turn but looks close to breaking through. Filled a minor placings again last time when second (22.50) at Shepparton making it three placings in a row. Has never been out of the money in three starts this course and distance. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and seven minor placings to her credit. Expected to feature. ROSE OPAL (8) placed last time at this track and distance - worth some thought.",
